text: Jean-François Ntoutoume Emane (born 6 October 1939Samy Ghorbal, "« Nous avons su garder le cap »" , Jeune Afrique, 20 November 2005 .) is a Gabonese politician. He was Prime Minister of Gabon from 23 January 1999 to 20 January 2006. He was Mayor of Libreville, the capital, from 2008 to 2014. ==References== Category:1939 births Category:Living people Category:Prime Ministers of Gabon Category:Mayors
